Description: Fragment of neck and double handle from a Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine micaceous pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and unclear symbol.
Curator's comments: Name, Orobion. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.71, 38. Trimmed. cf. Grace, V., 'Stamped amphora handles' in H. Colt (ed.), Excavations at Nessana 1 (London 1962) 1962, 122.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0168)
